  "prompt": "I mean, money laundering is definitely illegal, isn't it?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is **definitely illegal** in virtually every country. It involves disguising the origins of illegally obtained money (often from activities like drug trafficking, fraud, or corruption) to make it appear as if it came from legitimate sources. Laws and regulations are in place globally to combat money laundering, and those found guilty of it can face severe penalties, including hefty fines, asset seizure, and imprisonment.\n\nFor example, in the United States, the **Bank Secrecy Act (BSA)** and the **Patriot Act** are key pieces of legislation aimed at preventing money laundering. Similarly, international frameworks like the **Financial Action Task Force (FATF)** set global standards to combat money laundering and terrorist financing.\n\nIf you have specific concerns or questions about this topic, feel free to ask!",
